'''Ibrahim Mohammad Sami Sadeh''' ({{langx|ar|إبراهيم سعادة}}; born 27 April 2000) is a Jordanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Iraqi Stars League]] side [[Al-Karma SC|Al-Karma]] and the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=سعادة ينضم للمحرق البحريني قادما من الخور |url=https://alghad.com/Section-180/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%B3%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D9%86%D8%B6%D9%85-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%85%D8%A7-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%B1-1762902 |website=alghad.com |publisher=Al-Ghad |language=Arabic |date=17 July 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Sadeh debuted for the [[Jordan national football team|Jordan national team]] in a 2–0 friendly win over [[Tajikistan national football team|Tajikistan]] on 1 February 2021.<ref name="Global Sports Archive 2021">{{cite web | title=Match Report of Jordan vs Tajikistan – 2021-02-01 – FIFA Friendlies | website=Global Sports Archive | date=1 Jan 2021 | url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2021-02-01/jordan-vs-tajikistan/2277327/ | access-date=25 Mar 2021}}</ref>

In January 2024, Sadeh took part in the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] with Jordan.<ref>{{cite news|title=قائمة النشامى لنهائيات كأس آسيا 🇯🇴|trans-title=Al-Nashama list for the Asian Cup Finals 🇯🇴|url=https://twitter.com/JordanFA/status/1741356148530299195|publisher=Jordan Football Association|website=Twitter|date=31 December 2023|access-date=1 January 2024|language=ar}}</ref>

